IMPRESSION:
CERVICAL SPINE:
1. Numerous bilateral neural foraminal masses, left greater than right, with minimal interval increase in size. 


BRACHIAL PLEXUS NEUROGRAPHY:
1. Numerous bilateral brachial plexus and intercostal peripheral nerve sheath tumors, with minimal interval increase in size but without worrisome with ADC values (with the exception of left anterior scalene mass contiguous with the left C3-C4 foraminal 
mass and left larynx mass - limited due to failure of DWI in these regions but without early arterial enhancement). 


Images and interpretation personally reviewed by: SHIVANI AHLAWAT, MD
